# J.Crew Scraping

## Product Pages
- Product data lives in `#__NEXT_DATA__` as JSON under `props.initialState.products.productsByProductCode`
- Product name: `productsByProductCode[code].productName`
- Price: `productsByProductCode[code].colorsList[0].price.formatted`
- Fallback to `<meta property="og:title">` and `<meta property="product:price:amount">`

## Gallery Images
- Container: `[class*="product-gallery-container"]` (class `ProductGallery__product-gallery-container___`)
- Each image: `RevampedZoomImage__container___` > `.image-wrapper.portrait-mode` > `<img>`
- Only include images with `s7-img-facade` in the src (filters out marketing/nav images)
- Normalize to `?hei=1200` and strip `crop` param for full-res

## Image URL Pattern
`https://www.jcrew.com/s7-img-facade/{productCode}_{colorCode}{suffix}`

| Suffix | Type | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| (none) | model | Main product shot, model on body |
| `_m` | model | Model alternate angle |
| `_ed`, `_edm` | model | Editorial model shot |
| `_d1`, `_d2`, `_d3` | detail | Close-up / fabric detail |
| `_flat` | flat | Flat lay |
| `_sw` | swatch | Color swatch thumbnail (never in gallery) |

## Category Pages
- Category pages (e.g. `/c/mens_category/sweaters`) have `__NEXT_DATA__` with product URLs
- Extract via regex: `/"\/p\/[^"]+"/g` from the JSON blob
- Individual product pages must use full path URLs (not just product codes)
